oc:kn_6bb63f02 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring skill content for a plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Skills should use progressive disclosure — keep SKILL.md lean and focused on core concepts, move detailed information to references/ and examples/ subdirectories that load only when needed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Progressive disclosure manages context window usage, loading only the depth of information required for the current task rather than overwhelming the agent with everything at once." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_81a5431f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing agents that need domain-specific knowledge" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Agents should reference relevant skills for project-specific guidelines — e.g., a code-reviewer agent loads the code-standards skill, and a test-generator agent loads the testing-patterns skill." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Skills provide contextual knowledge loaded on demand, keeping agent definitions lean while ensuring they operate with project-specific conventions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_cf01b2e4 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a production-ready Claude Code plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A standard plugin should include commands, agents, skills, and hooks organized in separate top-level directories with auto-discovery, plus a complete plugin.json manifest with all recommended metadata fields." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multiple coordinated components provide richer user interaction patterns — commands for explicit invocation, agents for automatic task delegation, skills for contextual knowledge, and hooks for automated enforcement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d418e5de a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing any file within the plugin from commands, hooks, agents, or skills" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for all intra-plugin path references in hook commands, script execution, and MCP server arguments — never hardcode absolute paths or use relative paths from working directory." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Plugins install in different locations depending on OS, user preferences, and installation method. Hardcoded paths break portability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ea784865 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing hooks for code quality or compliance enforcement" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use hooks to enforce standards automatically — PreToolUse hooks can validate code changes against style guides before writing, and Stop hooks can run quality checks before task completion." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Automated enforcement through hooks ensures consistent quality without relying on manual checks, catching issues at the earliest possible moment." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

